HEADWORD: Poind
<hw>Poind</hw> <pr>(poind)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Pound</er> to confine.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To impound, as cattle.</def> <mark>[Obs. or Scot.]</mark>  <rj><au>Flavel.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To distrain.</def> <mark>[Scot.]</mark>  <rj><au>Sir W. Scott.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

